gurmukhi: ਰਣੰ ਜੀਤਿ ਅਾੲੇ || ਜਯੰ ਗੀਤ ਗਾੲੇ ||
transliteration: Ranan Jeet(i) Aae|| Jayan Goot Gade||
translation: We returned after victory and sang songs of triumph.

gurmukhi: ਧਨੰ ਧਾਰ ਬਰਖੇ || ਸਬੈ ਸੂਰ ਹਰਖੇ ||੩੫||
transliteration: Dhanan Dhaar Barkhe|| Sabai Soor Harkhe||35||
translation: I showered wealth on the warriors, who were full of rejoicings.35.

gurmukhi: ਜੁਧ ਜੀਤ ਅਾੲੇ ਜਬੈ ਟਿਕੈ ਨ ਤਿਨ ਪੁਰ ਪਾਂਵ ||
transliteration: Judh Jeet Aae Jabai Tikai Na Tin Pur Paanv||
translation: When I returned after victory, I did not remain at Paonta.

gurmukhi: ਕਾਹਲੂਰ ਮੈਂ ਬਾਂਧਿਯੋ ਅਾਨ ਅਾਨੰਦਪੁਰ ਗਾਂਵ ||੩੬||
transliteration: Kaahloor Main Baandhiyo Aan Aanandpur Gadnv||36||
translation: I came to Kahlur and established the village Anandpur.36.

gurmukhi: ਜੇ ਜੇ ਨਰ ਤਹ ਨ ਭਿਰੇ ਦੀਨੇ ਨਗਰ ਨਿਕਾਰ ||
transliteration: Je Je Nar Tah Nab Hire Doone Nagad Nikaar||
translation: Those, who did not join the forces, were turned out from the town.

gurmukhi: ਜੇ ਤਿਹ ਠੳੁਰ ਭਲੇ ਭਿਰੇ ਤਿਨੈ ਕਰੀ ਪ੍ਰਤਿਪਾਰ ||੩੭||
transliteration: Je Tih Thaur Bhale Bhire Tinai Daroo Pratipaar||37||
translation: And those who fought bravely were patronized by me 37.

gurmukhi: ਬਹੁਤ ਦਿਵਸ ੲਿਹ ਭਾਂਤਿ ਬਿਤਾੲੇ || ਸੰਤ ੳੁਬਾਰ ਦੁਸਟ ਸਭ ਘਾੲੇ ||
transliteration: Bahout Divas Ih Bhaant(i) Bitaae|| Sant Oubaar Doust Sabh Ghaae||
translation: Many days passed in this way, he saints were protected and the wicked persons were killed.

gurmukhi: ਟਾਂਗ ਟਾਂਗ ਕਰਿ ਹਨੇ ਨਿਦਾਨਾ || ਕੂਕਰ ਜਿਮਿ ਤਿਨ ਤਜੇ ਪਰਾਨਾ ||੩੮||
transliteration: Taan Taan Kar(i) Hane Nidaanaa|| Kookar Jim(i) Tin Taje Paraanaa||38||
translation: The tyrants were hanged ultimately killed, they breathed their last like dogs.38.

gurmukhi: ੲਿਤਿ ਸ੍ਰੀ ਬਚਿਤ੍ਰ ਨਾਟਕ ਗ੍ਰੰਥੇ ਭੰਗਾਣੀ ਜੁੱਧ ਬਰਨਨੰ ਨਾਮ ਅਸਟਮੋ ਧਿਅਾੲਿ ਸਮਾਪਤ ਮਸਤੁ ਸੁਭ ਮਸਤੁ ||੮|| ਅਫਜੂ ||੩੨੦||
transliteration: It(i) Sri Bachitra Naatak Granthe Bhanadaanoo Juddh Barnanan Naam Astmo Dhiaae Samaapat Mast(u) Soubh Mast(u)||8||afjoo||320||
translation: End of the Eighth Chapter of BACHITTAR NATAK entitled ‘Description of the Battle of Bhangani.’8.320.
Here begins the Description of the Battle of Nadaun:
